NOTICE

This dataset is derived from the VU Amsterdam Metaphor Corpus (VUAMC).

Original source:
Steen, Gerard J., Aletta G. Dorst, J. Berenike Herrmann, Anna A. Kaal,
Tina A. J. Prins, and Gitte Kristiansen. (2010).
Metaphor in Usage: The VU Amsterdam Metaphor Corpus.
Amsterdam/Philadelphia: John Benjamins.

The VUAMC itself is based on material from the British National Corpus (BNC).

Available at:
https://ota.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/repository/xmlui/handle/20.500.12024/2541?show=full



BNC Licence:
Available for non-commercial use on condition that the terms of the BNC Licence
are observed and that this header is included in its entirety with any copy distributed.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This repository provides a parsed and reformatted version of the VUAMC dataset.
The modifications include parsing the XML source, alignment with book appendix
figures, token-level restructuring, and identification of discrepancies between
the XML and published counts.

These modifications are released under the
Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License (CC BY-SA 4.0).
See: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Copyright (c) 2025 [Daban Q. Jaff]

